#
# NPU Patch Explanation:
# 
# 1. Mock device capability: torch.cuda.get_device_capability = lambda *args, **kwargs: (10, 0)
#    - NPU is not a CUDA device, so get_device_capability() returns None
#    - This mock makes NPU appear as SM 10.0 device, enabling all SM tests
#
# 2. Null check for all SM version judgments:
#    - Added "is not None" check before comparison to prevent TypeError
#    - Prevents "None >= tuple" errors when running on NPU
#
# 3. Coverage: 12 SM version judgments (SM53-SM120 + IS_SM89/90/100/12X)
#    - PyTorch 2.12.0 adds new SM versions (SM100, SM120)
#    - All judgments need null check for NPU compatibility
#
# 4. Key SM versions:
#    - SM 5.3: Maxwell architecture (GTX 750)
#    - SM 6.0: Pascal architecture (GTX 1080)
#    - SM 7.0: Volta architecture (Tesla V100)
#    - SM 8.0: Ampere architecture (RTX 3090)
#    - SM 9.0: Hopper architecture (H100)
#    - SM 10.0/12.0: Future architectures (Blackwell/Next-gen)
#